<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-15T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-15T00:00:00-05:00" n="820" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d820">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/12497.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Brazilian Minister</gloss> to
                                Mexico to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Brazilian Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico City</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-15">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 15, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>84. This afternoon General Huerta will resign and Carbajal, the Minister
                            for Foreign Affairs mentioned in my 82, July 10, will take possession as
                            Provisional President, with best disposition to facilitate arrangements
                            for the pacification. Department’s views will be highly appreciated.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Cardoso de Oliveira</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>